<h1>Technology in the Classroom</h1>
[/fusion_text][fusion_text]In today's world it is critical to integrate technological resources and information into the classroom environment. There are a number of ways and technologies that enable this. For instance, SMART Boards enhance education with interactive white boards. The following resources describe how to bring technology into the classroom and how to use technology to enhance lesson plans.
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://blogs.region4.nycenet.edu/communities/smartboard/default.aspx" rel="nofollow">Integrating Whiteboard Technology</a> SMART Boards in the Classroom</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.sachem.edu/dept/sd/smartboard/Elementary%20Resources.htm" rel="nofollow">Smart Board Sites</a> Resources for Elementary Schools</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.clemson.edu/ccit/support_services/it_support/computer_training/04_classroom_tech/06_smartboads/index.html" rel="nofollow">Classroom Technology</a> How to Use A SMART Board</li>
	<li><a href="http://commfaculty.fullerton.edu/jreinard/internet.htm" rel="nofollow">Internet Research</a> Resources regarding research online</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/TeachingLib/Guides/Internet/FindInfo.html" rel="nofollow">Finding Information on the Web</a> From the University of California at Berkeley</li>
	<li><a href="http://nces.ed.gov/pubsearch/pubsinfo.asp?pubid=2003313" rel="nofollow">Technology in Schools</a> Guidelines from NCES</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.cet.edu/?cat=cotf" rel="nofollow">Classroom of the Future</a> From the Center for Educational Technologies</li>
	<li><a href="http://etc.usf.edu/te/" rel="nofollow">Tech Ease</a> Questions &amp; Answers About Classroom Technology</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.its2.uidaho.edu/tec/nwacc/nwacc.htm" rel="nofollow">Effective Support for Classroom Technology</a> An Overview</li>
	<li><a href="http://www2.lib.uchicago.edu/~llou/forintlaw.html" rel="nofollow">Legal Issues on the Web</a> Legal Issues When Using the Web as a Reference</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.nyu.edu/projects/nissenbaum/ethics_bru_full.html" rel="nofollow">Internet Research Ethnics</a>- From New York University</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.cc.gatech.edu/~asb/ethics/" rel="nofollow">Online Research</a> Ethical Guidelines</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.internet2.edu/about/" rel="nofollow">Internet 2</a> How the next Generation of the Internet Affects Education</li>
